{"name": "replaceapplemusic", "metadata": {"name": "replaceapplemusic", "version": "0.0.2", "classifiers": ["Operating System :: MacOS", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/realtvop/ReplaceAppleMusic", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["appscript", "mutagen"], "summary": "A Python utility to replace source files of songs in Apple Music while preserving metadata", "upload_time": 1735235984}, "documentation": ["# ReplaceAppleMusic\n\nA Python utility to replace source files of songs in Apple Music while preserving metadata like play count, favorite status, and playlist memberships.\n\n## Features\n\n- Preserves play count\n- Maintains favorite status\n- Keeps playlist memberships\n- Automatically removes old track after replacement\n\n## Requirements\n\n- macOS\n- Python 3.x\n- Apple Music app\n\n## Installation\n\nYou can install it directly from PyPI:\n```bash\npip install replaceapplemusic\n```\n\nOr install from source:\n1. Clone this repository\n2. Install dependencies:\n```bash\npip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n3. Make sure Apple Music is running and you have the necessary permissions\n\n## Usage\n\n```bash\n# Replace a song\nramusic /path/to/new/file.m4a\n\n# Replace songs in a folder\nramusic /path/to/folder\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "bridge", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "bridge.get_song_info", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "track_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "artist", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "album", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bridge.replace_song", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "track", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "bridge.app", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bridge.playlists", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "main", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "main.print_help", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "main.process_folder", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "folder_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "folder", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "main.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "file_reader", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "file_reader.read_m4a_metadata", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "file_reader.process_folder", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "folder_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "file_reader.process_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "file_reader.get_songs_in_folder", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "folder_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}]}